((SELECT id FROM "legacy".crops WHERE label = 'Clover, Crimson' and zone = 7),(SELECT id FROM "legacy".data_keys WHERE key = 'cover_crop_description'),'A cool season annual with a short, upright growth habit. Popular in warmer regions of the Northeast. Shade tolerant. Does not reliably overwinter. Good forage producer, good N-fixer. Showy red blooms, good for pollinators. Host to some problem nematodes. Inoculate the seed with appropriate Rhizobium spp.; cross-inoculates with red or white clover. Mixes well with barley, annual ryegrass, cereal rye. Larger seeded and better seedling vigor than most clovers. Earlier-seeded, more fall growth, earlier spring bloom than hairy vetch. Slower residue breakdown of stems and N release than vetch.'),
